The reason for dropping columns is few are redundant and few has missing values more than 60 %¶
  • In few columns we can infer data by comparing with with other columns,"OCCUPATION_TYPE" can be filled by comparing data at "NAME_INCOME_TYPE".
  • But as we can get insights directly from "NAME_INCOME_TYPE" which is higly depedant,we have dropped "OCCUPATION_TYPE".

Client_Data["DAYS_EMPLOYED"].replace(to_replace=1000,value=70,inplace=True)

Conclusion:¶

8% were Defaulters out of 3Lakh Applicants.

Data_Discrepancies:

  • AMT_INCOME column has income ranging from 6-120 Millions, but the credit amount 5% which is concern factor.
  • Few Records in Days Employeed has crossed max 70 years, they were imputed with 70.

Findings:

  • Maximum loans sanctioned were Cash loans.
  • Highest Applicants are female, but deafuters were high in Male.
  • Risk is less with applicants who are having either car or Own House.
  • Applicants in Rented houses and Pensioners are of high risk.
  • Risk is high with Single parent applicants
  • Maximum Defaulters lie in Age group of 25-30.
  • Maximum Defaulters has employee experince < 5years, but the risk lies with <1 year Experience Employees.
  • Most Applicants and defaulters fall under Income range of 40K and 2.5 Lakhs.
